need information about the convict ship the lady shore circa the lady shore due to australia arrived in south america in about and got to the port of monevideo is this information correct the first fleet of convict ships sailed for australia in arriving but the lady shore was not one of them the lady shore a ton ship built in hull in sailed from gravesend in may with female convicts plus one male bound for port jackson nsw the voyage was never completed having replenished supplies en route at rio de janeiro members of the crew of the lady shore mutinied on the night of st august the mutiny was not successful but there were insufficient numbers of loyal sailors remaining to attempt the perilous passage to australia as a result the lady shore docked at montevideo unloading its cargo of convicts there they were then disposed off as servants semi slaves for rich residents of montevideo First Fleet USS Tuscaloosa (CA-37) USS Waters (DD-115) USS Wichita (CA-45) USS Alamo Ferdinand Magellan USS Wadsworth (DD-516) USS West Virginia (BB-48) USS Arthur W. Radford (DD-968) USS Wrangell (AE-12) USS Ticonderoga (CV-14) USS America (CV-66) USS Utah (BB-31) USS Thompson (DD-627) USS Idaho (BB-42) USS Ammen (DD-527) USS Wickes (DD-578) USS Augusta (CA-31) Mutiny on the Bounty USS Missouri (BB-63) USS Taussig (DD-746) USS Walke (DD-723) USS Atlanta (CL-51) Francis Drake USS William B. Preston (DD-344) USS Chicago (CA-136) USS Wallace L. Lind (DD-703) USS Fletcher (DD-445) USS San Francisco (CA-38) Norfolk Island USS Vesuvius (AE-15) USS Shenandoah (1862) USS Alfred A. Cunningham (DD-752) USS Uhlmann (DD-687) USS Vestal (AR-4) Second Fleet (Australia) Sydney USS Turner Joy (DD-951) USS Atule (SS-403) USS Aylwin (DD-355) USS Yorktown (CV-5) USS Indianapolis (CA-35) HMS Electra (H27) USS Vancouver (LPD-2) USS Wilkes (DD-441) USS Twining (DD-540) USS Enterprise (CV-6) Invergordon Mutiny USS Anderson (DD-411) Ship USS Washington (ACR-11) USS Washington (BB-56) History of Victoria USS Alt